gle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zno1665702976446.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zno1665702976446.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zno1665702976446.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zno1665702976446\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Primary Key and Physical Row Addresses\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zno1665702976446__primary_key_and_physical_row_addresses_178180\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A DBMS connector needs to uniquely identify each record, either by means of a primary key or a unique identification based on a physical access technique.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zno1665702976446__p_d62036e1_d62037e1_d62038e1\">Uniface adheres to the relational model, so every table accessed by Uniface must defined within Uniface as having a primary key. A record is uniquely identified by means of the field or fields that constitute the primary key. Uniface enforces the uniqueness of each record in a table via the primary key.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zno1665702976446__p_d62039e1_d62040e1_d62041e1\">Some DBMSs support the use of primary keys to uniquely identify each record. Connectors for these DBMSs use primary keys to locate records.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zno1665702976446__p_d62042e1_d62043e1_d62044e1\">Alternatively, some DBMSs support a unique identification based on a physical access technique. Uniface uses the generic term <dfn class=\"term\">Physical Row Address</dfn> (PRA) for this feature. Uniface is capable of using PRAs. Generally, using PRAs improves performance.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534524\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534524\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Primary Key and Physical Row Addresses Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Primary Key and Physical Row Addresses A DBMS connector needs to uniquely identify each record, either by means of a primary key or a unique identification based on a physical access technique. Uniface adheres to the relational model, so every table accessed by Uniface must defined within Uniface as having a primary key. A record is uniquely identified by means of the field or fields that constitute the primary key. Uniface enforces the uniqueness of each record in a table via the primary key. Some DBMSs support the use of primary keys to uniquely identify each record. Connectors for these DBMSs use primary keys to locate records. Alternatively, some DBMSs support a unique identification based on a physical access technique. Uniface uses the generic term Physical Row Address (PRA) for this feature. Uniface is capable of using PRAs. Generally, using PRAs improves performance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}